product_name: MaybellineInstant Age Rewind Eraser Dark Circle Treatment Concealer
summary: SummaryHighlightsVeganGive BackMaybelline Instant Eraser is America's #1 concealer* and does it all in just a click - it conceals dark circles, correct blemishes, and contours.
details: DetailsBenefitsUp to 12HR moisturizing wear & crease-resistant coverageQuickly covers up blemishes or dark spots to transform your look instantlySponge tip applicator lets you apply with ease in a clickFeaturesInfused with Goji berry & Haloxyl to create a radiant refreshed looking eye areaOil-freeFragrance-freeNon-comedogenic & suitable for sensitive skin.*L'Oreal calculation based in part on data reported by NielsenIQ through its Scantrack Service for the Concealer category for the 52-week period ending July 31, 2021, for the US xAOC market according to L'Oreal's custom product hierarchy. Copyright 2021, Nielsen Consumer LLC.Item 2547762How To UseStep 1. Twist the sponge applicator in direction of arrows until the concealer is visible on the sponge.Step 2. Apply concealer directly to the under-eye area, blending in an outward motion.Step 3. For extreme dark circles, apply the Neutralizer shade under concealer shade.Step 4. For a luminous touch, apply the Brightener shade to the inner corner of eyes, brow bones and bridge of the nose.The Dark Circles Eraser is protected by an anti-microbial system. Do not wet applicator. Wipe off excess eye concealer with dry tissue.IngredientsAqua/Water/Eau, Cyclopentasiloxane, Dimethicone, Isododecane, Glycerin, PEG-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Butylene Glycol, Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Nylon-12, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Cyclohexasiloxane, PEG-10 Dimethicone, Cetyl PEG/PPG-10/1 Dimethicone, Phenoxyethanol, Sodium Chloride, Polyglyceryl-4 Isostearate, Caprylyl Glycol, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Ethylhexylglycerin, Methylparaben, Lycium Barbarum Fruit Extract, Chlorphenesin, Ethylparaben, Aluminum Hydroxide, Steareth-20, Chlorhexidine Digluconate, N-Hydroxysuccinimide, Potassium Sorbate, Tocopherol, Palmitoyl Oligopeptide, Chrysin, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7. May Contain (+/-): CI 77891/Titanium Dioxide, CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499/Iron Oxides.
how_to_use: Step 1. Twist the sponge applicator in direction of arrows until the concealer is visible on the sponge.Step 2. Apply concealer directly to the under-eye area, blending in an outward motion.Step 3. For extreme dark circles, apply the Neutralizer shade under concealer shade.Step 4. For a luminous touch, apply the Brightener shade to the inner corner of eyes, brow bones and bridge of the nose.The Dark Circles Eraser is protected by an anti-microbial system. Do not wet applicator. Wipe off excess eye concealer with dry tissue.

reviews.headline: Good concealer
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I really enjoyed this concealer.  The coverage was incredible and it didn't really crease on my under eye area. I definitely recommend trying this out!

reviews.headline: Lovely
reviews.comments: A wonderful concealer from Maybelline that I have been using for a long time. It masks dark circles under the eyes, and also if you have any imperfections, be sure to apply it and it will mask everything as if you have nothing on your face. Doesn't roll or tighten the skin, works all day and looks great. Smells nice and is easy to use thanks to the soft roller on top. Nice price and will suit even the most fastidious.

reviews.headline: covers redness very well!
reviews.comments: This color corrector is amazing for any redness or hyperpigmentation before applying concealer or foundation. It really works to even out your complexion upon makeup application. It also works for dark under eyes as well. For the price of this product to work for so many uses is so worth it!

reviews.headline: Concealer
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I love the fact that this concealer has a nice fluffy sponge already built in. It makes it really easy to use on the go. It covers well, but I found it to settle into my wrinkles a little more than I'd like.

reviews.headline: Flawless concealer!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This concealer truly lives up to the hype! The sponge applicator makes it so easy to apply and the formula blends effortlessly for a smooth, brightened finish. It covers dark circles without creasing and feels lightweight all day. Perfect for a natural yet refreshed look!!

reviews.headline: Great convenient coverage!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The Maybelline Instant Age Rewind ERASER is a multi-use concealer with great medium buildable coverage. It is scent-free and comes in a convenient-sized packaging for throwing in a makeup bag or a pair for on the go! It handles really well on under eye bags and pretty much cancels and blue/purple discoloration (like undereye bags).  The concealer goes on very blendable and dries down nicely for a long-lasting wear. There's a little bit of a learning curve on the first application with the sponge, you don't realize it's saturated until it's too late. But after the first saturation of the applicator,  any to follow is super easy to use! It was easy to match my shade and I could imagine doing a full contoured face with the range of shades available!

reviews.headline: Medium Coverage
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I wish I could've tried a darker color but for the most part it blends smooth. It seemed to be medium coverage. It was packaged really well. I'd try it again to try my shade.

reviews.headline: One of my fav
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I've been using the Maybelline Instant Age Rewind Concealer and I really like it. The sponge tip makes it super easy to apply, and it blends out nicely without looking heavy. It gives me good coverage for dark circles and little spots but still looks natural on the skin. I like that it feels lightweight and doesn't crease too much throughout the day. It's definitely one of those everyday concealers that's quick to use and makes a big difference.

reviews.headline: Easy Peasy!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This will forever be super easy to apply and just blends into the skin so nicely. So easy to used for a fast make up look or just to apply on spots where you might want to cover some redness like me.

reviews.headline: Love
reviews.comments: My dark circles disappeared with this concealer what a nice coverage you get for a fraction of the price blended nicely with my beauty blender and the packaging was simple and easy to use

reviews.headline: A classic for a reason!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I was excited to try this product since my mom did tell me about it, she said it worked magic. I was surprised to see she was quite right! The product is amazing, it has great blendability and it does the work of covering greatly the undereyes. I completely recommend it as a great drugstore alternative

reviews.headline: Average concealer
reviews.comments: This concealer was I think perhaps too light/white for me. It had medium coverage and did cover what I desired but I didn't love the finish. I do like the built in dabbing brush but still kept like I needed a beauty blender

reviews.headline: Great applicator/coverage
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Great coverage just wrong color for my skin. I would get a regular skin color over the green in my case, so just think about what's best for your skin tone. I enjoy the applicator the most on this product.

reviews.headline: Surprised how well it works.
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I'm actually surprised how well it worked. I have terrible dark circles. I used to use this when I was a teen and don't remember it working this well. It definitely seems to have been improved. Great and easy to use packaging, no scent. Finish is great but I'd set with powder. Love it though!

reviews.headline: Best concealer
reviews.comments:
The Instant Age Rewind Concealer has quickly become one of my all-time favorite makeup products! The formula is lightweight but has amazing coverage—it brightens my under-eye area instantly and makes me look more awake without feeling heavy or cakey.

The sponge applicator is super convenient and blends the product really well, so I don't even need a brush or sponge most days. I love how smooth and natural it looks on the skin—it doesn't settle into fine lines or crease, which has been a problem for me with other concealers.

Another huge plus is that it lasts all day without needing touch-ups. I can wear it for work, errands, or even a night out, and it still looks fresh hours later. The shade range is great too, so it's easy to find a match or even pick up a lighter shade for brightening.

reviews.headline: Will continue to buy this product!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I used to use this years ago but do not remember it working this well for my skin. I have dry, sensitive skin and this applies wonderfully under my eyes. Concealers are often very difficult for me to find, because they usually cake up or are very patchy. This blends beautifully and is super easy to use. I love the applicator because it allows the product to stay clean. Other concealers usually leak or drip all over the bottle for me.

reviews.headline: Great concealer
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This is my regular concealer that I have been using for the past 4 years. Its has great texture and covers all the needed areas. Blends in great with my skin tone.

reviews.headline: Affordable and effective
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Maybelline Instant Age Rewind Eraser Color Correcting Concealer is lightweight, blendable, and does the job without looking cakey. The sponge tip makes application quick and easy, and the formula melts into the skin for a natural finish. It brightens dark circles, tones down redness, and adds just enough coverage for a fresh, awake look. Works well alone for minimal makeup days or under foundation for extra correction. Affordable and effective—definitely a solid drugstore staple.

reviews.headline: Good Product, Don't love the applicator
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This product worked well, it was good concealer, brightened below my eyes well. The spongy applicator is interesting, but I'm not convinced of its usefulness. It seems to put a lot of product on it, but then you need another sponge without product to blend it out

faceoff_positive.comments: After several tries of the vast array of concealers past years, FINALLY found this product while out browsing/shopping. It has to be new. Instead of a typical under eye remedy cover ...perhaps I was looking not in the right direction, so-to- speak, but, instead thought a much I needed correctiveness. So, I purchased this product. Rushed home, placed in on my under eyes and wham! Away went the dark holloweness and my tired eyes literally popped with youthfulness! Included a photo for you to see Left eye WITH product/Right eye WITHOUT.  Beyond thrilled with the results ....pure ecstatic happiness! I am 53, blonde hair, light/med peachy pinky  skin tone.
faceoff_positive.headline: Best yet!

faceoff_negative.comments: I love the smooth application, love the color (charcoal) and love how long it last on my eyes.BUT...I tried every method suggested to sharpen the tip after two weeks of use and the design and composition (hard plastic) of this pencil totally sucks!  I bought 3 different cosmetic sharpeners and just when I thought I was making progress, the tip of the eyeliner broke off.  I read every review here when I couldn't figure out how to get more product out.  I followed all the suggestions - this item is going in the trash and I will go back to Ulta Waterproof eyeliner.  Do not waste your money on this product until they make it in a twist holder.
faceoff_negative.headline: Useless after 2 weeks!
